    public class LinkedList<T>
extends ChainedIndexedDataStructure<T>
    Basic implementation of Doubly Linked List Time Complexity: Time will be measured in either direct and indirect recursive method calls or loop iterations (where applicable). create() = O(n)
    insert() = O(n)
    search() = O(n)
    remove() = O(n)
    Space complexity: Space will be measured in number of auxiliary nodes or variables that are allocated within a given method. Values passed as parameters that are on the call stack are not included.
